    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5fe02d63_b36b1b0f",
        "filename": "resultdb/cli/cmd_stream.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 125,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-28T23:01:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "uint is simpler for the usage message, because the usage shows the type.\n\n```\n$ rdb stream --help\nUsage:  rdb stream [flags] TEST_CMD [TEST_ARG]...\n  -max-concurrent-artifact-uploads uint\n        The maximum ...\n```\n\nIf int is used, then the usage message should describe that negative values are not acceptable, although the type allows negative values.\n\nAs per the upper limit, whatever limit the dispatcher.Options allows is the upper limit?\nI am not sure if it\u0027s necessary to enforce an upper limit.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "2aaab49f_82090e67",
      "revId": "c11643ecd5b61cc93904ce5272b01db641e321db",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
